main event: Two oval-shaped objects of blue and red light were reported hovering about 50-75 feet off the ground for around 1-1/2 minutes in South Tewksbury, Massachusetts on August 30, 1960.
interesting points: One object was larger than the other.
The objects disappeared after about 1-1/2 minutes of observation.
The Air Technical Intelligence Center was unable to determine the nature of the report.
A similar sighting had been reported by the witness on a previous occasion.
The report includes a handwritten letter providing further details and explanations about the sighting.
sighted object: Two oval-shaped objects emitting blue and red light
